  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As part of ACF&apos;s strategy the intervention aims to contribute to improving the WASH status of the targeted communities and reducing undernutrition. ACF will work with the communities and the established local governance structures to deliver an integrated WASH package to the families with malnourished children and PLW. ACF will employ community led approaches as the key means for sustainably addressing poor sanitation and stimulate the uptake of good hygiene practices. As such, community user groups (Community Volunteers, WUC, PMA, Mother to Mother Support Groups and Children Hygiene Clubs in schools) will be trained to create an avenue for sustainable service delivery and to build the resilience of local communities.</narrative>
  </description>
